The Proposal -
Financial stability of farmers if farmers' fruit crops are insured against weather hazards
Priority in the state is to help with the maintenance of a well-designed climate-resilient ecosystem.
Insurance schemes are being implemented. Various weather hazards adversely affect the productivity of the fruit.
This results in a large-scale decline in production. Alternately, the farmers do not get the expected yield.
All these factors are taken into account to ensure that the farmers get fruitful compensation.
